e]], American playwright, journalist, and diplomat, [[United States Ambassador to Italy]] (d. 1987)\n*  1903   &ndash; [[Edward Bawden]], British artist and illustrator (d. 1989)\n*[[1914]] &ndash; [[Chandler Harper]], American golfer (d. 2004)\n*  1914   &ndash; [[K. P. Ratnam]], Sri Lankan academic and politician (d. 2010)\n*[[1915]] &ndash; [[Harry Bertoia]], Italian-American sculptor and furniture designer (d. 1978) \n*  1915   &ndash; [[Jo\u017ea Horvat]], Croatian writer (d. 2012) \n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Davie Fulton]], Canadian lawyer, judge, and politician (d. 2000)\n*[[1917]] &ndash; [[David Hare (artist)|David Hare]], American Surrealist artist, sculptor, photographer and painter (d. 1992)\n*[[1918]] &ndash; [[G\u00fcnther Rall]], German general and pilot (d. 2009)\n*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Marion Hutton]], American singer and actress (d. 1987)\n*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Alfred Peet]], Dutch-American businessman, founded [[Peet's Coffee & Tea]] (d. 2007)\n*  1920   &ndash; [[Boris Vian]], French author and playwright (d. 1959)\n*[[1922]] &ndash; [[Kiyoshi Yamashita]], Japanese painter (d. 1971)\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[Val Logsdon Fitch]], American physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2015)\n*[[1924]] &ndash; [[Judith Jones]], American literary and cookbook editor (d. 2017)\n*  1925   &ndash; [[Bob Lanier (politician)|Bob Lanier]], American lawyer, banker, and politician, 58th [[List of mayors of Houston|Mayor of Houston]] (d. 2014)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Marques Haynes]], American basketball player (d. 2015)\n*[[1927]] &ndash; [[Claude Laydu]], Belgian-French actor, producer, and screenwriter (d. 2011)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Paul Wunderlich]],  German painter, sculptor and graphic artist (d. 2010)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Sara Montiel]], Spanish actress (d. 2013)\n*  1928   &ndash; [[James Earl Ray]], American criminal; assassin of Martin Luther King Jr. (d. 1998)\n*[[1929]] &ndash; [[Sam Steiger]], American journalist and politician (d. 2012)\n*[[1930]] &ndash; [[S\u00e1ndor Iharos]], Hungarian runner (d. 1996)\n*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Georges Dor]], Canadian author, playwright, and composer (d. 2001)\n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[Marcia Falkender, Baroness Falkender]], English politician (d. 2019)\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Udupi Ramachandra Rao]], Indian physicist and engineer (d. 2017)\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Perunchithiranar (Tamil nationalist)|Perunchithiranar]], Tamil poet (d. 1995)\n*  1933   &ndash; [[Elizabeth Azcona Cranwell]], Argentinian poet and translator (d. 2004)\n*[[1934]] &ndash; [[Gergely Kulcs\u00e1r]], Hungarian javelin thrower and coach\n*[[1935]] &ndash; [[Graham Farmer]], Australian footballer and coach (d. 2019)\n*[[1936]] &ndash; [[Sepp Blatter]], Swiss businessman\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Alfredo Zitarrosa]], Uruguayan singer-songwriter and journalist (d. 1989)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[Norman Blake (American musician)|Norman Blake]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist\n*  1938   &ndash; [[Ieronymos II of Athens]], Greek archbishop\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Asghar Ali Engineer]], Indian activist and author (d. 2013)\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Hugh Johnson (wine writer)|Hugh Johnson]], English author and critic\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Irina Press]], Ukrainian-Russian hurdler and pentathlete (d. 2004)\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Chuck Norris]], American actor, producer, and martial artist\n*  1940   &ndash; [[David Rabe]], American playwright and screenwriter\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Peter Berresford Ellis]], English historian and author\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Gail North-Saunders]], Bahamian historian, archivist, and author who established the Bahamian National Archives\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Katharine Houghton]], American actress and playwright\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Madhavrao Scindia]], Indian politician, [[Minister of Railways (India)|Indian Minister of Railways]] (d. 2001)\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[G\u00e9rard Garouste]], French contemporary artist\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Mike Hollands]], Australian animator and director, founded [[Act3animation]]\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Jim Valvano]], American basketball player and coach (d. 1993)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Kim Campbell]], Canadian lawyer and politician, 19th [[Prime Minister of Canada]]\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Tom Scholz]], American rock musician ([[Boston (band)|Boston]]), songwriter, inventor, and engineer\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Austin Carr]], American basketball player and sportscaster\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Bill Buxton]], Canadian computer scientist and academic\n*  1949   &ndash; [[Barbara Corcoran]], American businesswoman and television personality\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Catherine Pugh]], American politician, 50th [[mayor of Baltimore]] \n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Morgan Tsvangirai]], Zimbabwean politician, 2nd [[Prime Minister of Zimbabwe]] (d. 2018)\n*[[1953]] &ndash; [[Paul Haggis]], Canadian director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Didier Barbelivien]], French singer-songwriter\n*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Toshio Suzuki (racing driver)|Toshio Suzuki]], Japanese race car driver\n*[[1956]] &ndash; [[Robert Llewellyn]], English actor, producer, and screenwriter\n*  1956   &ndash; [[Larry Myricks]], American long jumper and sprinter\n*[[1957]] &ndash; [[Osama bin Laden]], Saudi Arabian terrorist, founded [[al-Qaeda]] (d. 2011)\n*[[1958]] &ndash; [[Garth Crooks]], English footballer forward and sportscaster<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=1773|title=Garth Crooks|website=soccerbase.com|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Steve Howe (baseball)|Steve Howe]], American baseball player (d. 2006)\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Sharon Stone]], American actress and producer\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Laurel Clark]], American captain, physician, and astronaut (d. 2003)\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Bobby Petrino]], American football player and coach\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Jasmine Guy]], American actress, singer, and director\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Seiko Matsuda]], Japanese singer-songwriter and actress\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Jeff Ament]], American bass player and songwriter\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Felipe Ramos]], Mexican footballer and referee\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Rick Rubin]], American record producer, founded [[Def Jam Recordings]]\n*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Neneh Cherry]], Swedish singer-songwriter<ref>{{cite book|author=Colin Larkin|title=The Virgin Encyclopedia of Nineties Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=crs7AQAAIAAJ|year=2000|publisher=Virgin|isbn=978-0-7535-0427-7|page=86}}</ref>\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex]]\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Jojo Lastimosa]], Filipino basketball player and coach\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Nikola Mladenov]], Macedonian journalist (d. 2013)\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Toni Polster]], Austrian footballer and manager\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Jillian Richardson]], Canadian sprinter\n*  1965   &ndash; [[Rod Woodson]], American football player, coach, and sportscaster\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Edie Brickell]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1966   &ndash; [[Mike Timlin]], American baseball player\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Thio Li-ann]], Singaporean lawyer and academic\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Pavel Srn\u00ed\u010dek]], Czech footballer and coach (d. 2015)\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Matt Barlow]], American singer-songwriter \n*[[1971]] &ndash; [[Jon Hamm]], American actor and director\n*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Matt Kenseth]], American race car driver \n*  1972   &ndash; [[Timbaland]], American rapper and producer \n*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Jason Croker]], Australian rugby league player and coach\n*  1973   &ndash; [[Chris Sutton]], English footballer and manager\n*  1973   &ndash; [[Mauricio Taricco]], Argentinian footballer, full back and assistant manager<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=7801|title=Mauricio Taricco|website=soccerbase.com|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Cristi\u00e1n de la Fuente]], Chilean-American model, actor, and producer\n*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Jamie Arnold (basketball)|Jamie Arnold]], American-Israeli basketball player and coach\n*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Barbara Schett]], Austrian tennis player and sportscaster\n*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Robin Thicke]], American singer\n*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Camille (singer)|Camille]], French singer-songwriter and actress\n*  1978   &ndash; [[Neil Alexander]], Scottish footballer\n*  1978   &ndash; [[Benjamin Burnley]], American musician\n*[[1980]] &ndash; [[Lars Horntveth]], Norwegian saxophonist and composer \n*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Samuel Eto'o]], Cameroonian footballer and manager\n*  1981   &ndash; [[\u00c1ngel L\u00f3pez (footballer)|\u00c1ngel L\u00f3pez]], Spanish footballer\n*  1981   &ndash; [[Steven Reid]], English-Irish footballer and manager\n*[[1982]] &ndash; [[Kwame Brown]], American basketball player\n*  1982   &ndash; [[Keke Wyatt]], American singer-songwriter and actress\n*[[1983]] &ndash; [[\u00c9tienne Boulay]], Canadian football player\n*  1983   &ndash; [[Rafe Spall]], English actor\n*  1983   &ndash; [[Janet Mock]], American journalist, author, and activist\n*  1983   &ndash; [[Carrie Underwood]], American singer-songwriter and actress\n*[[1984]] &ndash; [[Ben May]], English footballer\n*  1984   &ndash; [[Olivia Wilde]], American actress and producer\n*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Lassana Diarra]], French footballer\n*  1985   &ndash; [[Casey Dienel]], American singer-songwriter and pianist\n*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Martellus Bennett]], American football player\n*  1987   &ndash; [[Greg Eastwood]], New Zealand rugby league player\n*  1987   &ndash; [[Tuukka Rask]], Finnish ice hockey player\n*  1987   &ndash; [[Liu Shishi]], Chinese actress and ballerina\n*  1987   &ndash; [[M\u0101ris \u0160trombergs]], Latvian BMX racer<ref>{{cite web|title=Maris Strombergs|url=https://www.olympic.org/maris-strombergs|publisher=International Olympic Committee|accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[Josh Hoffman]], Australian-New Zealand rugby league player\n*  1988   &ndash; [[Kang In-soo]], South Korean singer\n*  1988   &ndash; [[Ivan Rakiti\u0107]], Croatian football player\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Neeskens Kebano]], French-born Congolese international footballer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=58077|title=Neeskens Kebano|website=soccerbase.com|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n*  1992   &ndash; [[Emily Osment]], American actress, singer, and songwriter\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Jack Butland]], English footballer\n*[[1995]]  &ndash; [[DaeSean Hamilton]], American football player<ref> http://www.nfl.com/player/daeseanhamilton/2561002/profile</ref>\n*  1995    &ndash; [[Zach LaVine]], American basketball player<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uclabruins.com/sports/mens-basketball/roster/zach-lavine/2799|title=Zach LaVine|website=UCLA Bruins|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n*  1995   &ndash; [[Sergey Mozgov]], Russian ice dancer\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Belinda Bencic]], Swiss tennis player<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wtatennis.com/players/319001/belinda-bencic|title=Belinda Bencic|website=Women's Tennis Association|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- Please do not add yourself, non-notable people, fictional characters, or people without Wikipedia articles to this list. No red links, please. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence. If there are multiple people in the same birth year, put them in alphabetical order of surname. Do not trust \"this year in history\" websites for accurate date information. -->\n\n==Deaths==\n* [[483]] &ndash; [[Pope Simplicius]]\n* [[933]] &ndash; [[Li Renfu]], Chinese [[warlord]] and governor\n* [[948]] &ndash; [[Liu Zhiyuan]], [[Shatuo]] founder of the [[Later Han (Five Dynasties)|Later Han]] dynasty (b. 895)\n*[[1039]] &ndash; [[Odo of Gascony|Eudes, Duke of Gascony]]\n*[[1222]] &ndash; [[John I of Sweden|Johan Sverkersson]], king of Sweden since [[1216]] (b. 1201)\n*[[1289]] &ndash; [[Maud de Lacy, Countess of Hertford and Gloucester]], English noble (b. 1223)\n*[[1291]] &ndash; [[Arghun]